Add pre-commit support (#62)

commit.message:
Show filenames with errors in --check mode (#57)

* Show filenames with errors in --check mode

* Shorten line

Fix newline after printing "No issues detected" during check mode (#53)

* Fix newline after printing "No issues detected" during check mode

In check mode, we print "No issue detected" after checking a file, and if that file contains no errors. This leads to lines like:

No issues detected!No issues detected!No issues detected!

Add a \n to make this slightly better.

* Update expected output in unit tests

Add check argument (#45)

* Add check argument

By specifying the --check argument, the program will exit with a code of 1. This is useful if using as part of a CI pipeline that should fail if changes are neccesary

* Remove extra newlines

reflected exclude option when use glob (#44)

* apply exclude option when use glob

* add unit test for is_exclude_file

autoflake.py: Add --ignore-init-module-imports (#42)

When used, this new CLI argument will cause
autoflake to ignore unused imports when
checking any __init__.py files.

New tests have also been added to
accompany this new feature.

Closes https://github.com/myint/autoflake/issues/35
Add note about # noqa comments to disable autoflake in specific lines (#43)

standard_paths in plat_specific True and False (#33)

Have `standard_paths` look in both platform-specific and platform-independent directories.  Fixes issue #32.
Use `pip` to avoid CPython 3.7 bug on Travis CI

Drop Python 3.3, which has reached end-of-life

This corresponds with the upcoming change in `pyflakes`:

https://github.com/PyCQA/pyflakes/pull/322
Avoid multiline values when removing duplicate keys

Avoid parsing code when removing duplicate keys

Make use of the existing multi-pass processing. This is safer and
matches how we do things for the other filters.

Sort line numbers of duplicates

The logic of `get_occurrence_in_object()` previously assumed the input
line numbers were sorted.

This fixes #29.
Narrow how much we filter out complex cases
